definition: to increase the specified cruising speed/to pick up speed/to speed up
to carry (hanging down from the hand)/to lift/to put forward/to mention/to raise (an issue)/upwards character stroke/lifting brush stroke (in painting)/scoop for measuring liquid

sentences.english: But I'd rather speed it up and run , and I think we can do that.
sentences.chinese: 但我更喜欢提速开跑，我认为我们做得到的。

sentences.english: To get back up to speed, just hit the gas again.
sentences.chinese: 重新提速，您只需再一次踏下油门。

sentences.english: No, it just gets you there faster.
sentences.chinese: 不会，开车只是一种提速代步的工具。

sentences.english: Continuous casting low-temperature molten steel, micro-electricity of micro-micro-particle, and casting blank speeding-up and normal pouring.

sentences.english: When the other car passes you, you speed up and overtake on the right again.
sentences.chinese: 当这辆车超过你，你提速再从右侧超车。

sentences.english: China Securities Journal news, recently, the pace of State-owned Key Enterprises reform has been further accelerated.

sentences.english: If ever an animal needed to be fast, it is the slow loris.
sentences.chinese: 如果世界上也有动物需要提速的话，那就是懒猴了。

sentences.english: Run the pickups at about your 5-K race pace.

sentences.english: The entire publishing life cycle has sped up in recent years.
sentences.chinese: 近些年，整个发行周期都提速了。

sentences.english: Each ship in the task force increased its speed to 25 knots.
sentences.chinese: 特遣舰队的每一个舰只都提速至25节。

sentences.english: Most of this speed-up can be attributed to better utilizing the hard disk.
sentences.chinese: 绝大多数的此类提速可归功于更好地利用硬盘。

sentences.english: China is to boost its train speed for the sixth time next Wednesday.
sentences.chinese: 中国火车将在下个星期三第六次大提速。
